    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix NGAP interface handling error due to incorrect scheduler pre-processor reset\n\n### Summary\nThe `dlsch_scheduler_pre_processor_reset_fairRR` function in the eNB scheduler was being called incorrectly within nested loops for each UE and CC, causing downstream procedure failures in the NGAP interface. This led to inconsistent scheduling states and potential race conditions.\n\nThis fix moves the function call outside the loops to ensure proper initialization.\n\n### Changes\n- `openair2/LAYER2/MAC/eNB_scheduler_fairRR.c`: Removed nested loops and called `dlsch_scheduler_pre_processor_reset_fairRR` only once per scheduling cycle.\n\n### Reproduction\nUnder load with multiple UEs, the gNB would experience intermittent failures in RRC connection establishment procedures. Error logs showed \"NGAP procedure failed\" messages correlating with scheduler timeouts. Memory usage would also increase steadily over time due to the repeated allocations.\n\nThe issue was reproducible by connecting 8+ UEs simultaneously and observing NGAP procedure failures within 5-10 minutes of operation.\n"
}